[32m+[m[32m# ADR-011 — REST API Architecture[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Status:** Accepted[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Date:** 23 July 2026[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Sprint:** Sprint 8 — REST API Integration[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Version:** v8.0.0[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Context[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPrior to Sprint 8, AnalystGPT Enterprise could only be executed[m
[32m+[m[32mthrough direct Python execution using the Application Layer.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAlthough the internal architecture was modular, reusable, and[m
[32m+[m[32mwell-tested, there was no standardized mechanism for external[m
[32m+[m[32msystems to invoke the analytics pipeline.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mFuture roadmap items including:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Power BI Integration[m
[32m+[m[32m- React Frontend[m
[32m+[m[32m- AI Services[m
[32m+[m[32m- External Integrations[m
[32m+[m[32m- Production Deployment[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mall require a stable service interface.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe existing architecture already isolated orchestration inside the[m
[32m+[m[32mApplication Layer, making it possible to introduce a Presentation[m
[32m+[m[32mLayer without modifying business modules.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Decision[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroduce a dedicated REST API Layer using FastAPI.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe REST API Layer becomes a Presentation Layer responsible only[m
[32m+[m[32mfor HTTP communication.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe layer is intentionally thin.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mResponsibilities include:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Request validation[m
[32m+[m[32m- Response serialization[m
[32m+[m[32m- Endpoint routing[m
[32m+[m[32m- Dependency Injection[m
[32m+[m[32m- OpenAPI generation[m
[32m+[m[32m- Swagger documentation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBusiness logic remains exclusively inside the Application Layer.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mPipeline execution continues through:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mApplication.run()[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mNo business module is aware that REST APIs exist.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Architectural Flow[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```text[m
[32m+[m[32mClient[m
[32m+[m[32m      │[m
[32m+[m[32m      ▼[m
[32m+[m[32mREST API Layer[m
[32m+[m[32m      │[m
[32m+[m[32m      ▼[m
[32m+[m[32mApplication Layer[m
[32m+[m[32m      │[m
[32m+[m[32m      ▼[m
[32m+[m[32mBusiness Modules[m
[32m+[m[32m      │[m
[32m+[m[32m      ▼[m
[32m+[m[32mPersistence Layer[m
[32m+[m[32m      │[m
[32m+[m[32m      ▼[m
[32m+[m[32mDatabase[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Consequences[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Positive[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- External integrations become possible.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Business modules remain unchanged.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Stable HTTP contracts are introduced.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Interactive API documentation becomes automatic.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Future frontend applications can reuse existing services.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Power BI can consume analytics through REST.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Testing becomes simpler through endpoint validation.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Layered architecture is preserved.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Negative[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Additional architectural layer increases complexity.[m
[32m+[m[32m- API contracts must now be versioned carefully.[m
[32m+[m[32m- HTTP request/response lifecycle introduces serialization overhead.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Documentation must remain synchronized with implementation.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Alternatives Considered[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Direct Application Invocation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mRejected.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mReason:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWould tightly couple clients to internal Python implementation.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## GraphQL[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mRejected.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mReason:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mREST APIs provide simpler integration for current roadmap objectives[m
[32m+[m[32mincluding Power BI and external analytics platforms.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Business Logic Inside Routes[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mRejected.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mReason:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mViolates Separation of Concerns and Single Responsibility Principle.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Design Principles Preserved[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Separation of Concerns[m
[32m+[m[32m- SOLID[m
[32m+[m[32m- Single Responsibility Principle[m
[32m+[m[32m- Dependency Inversion[m
[32m+[m[32m- Layered Architecture[m
[32m+[m[32m- High Cohesion[m
[32m+[m[32m- Low Coupling[m
[32m+[m[32m- Stable Contracts[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Implementation Impact[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mNew architectural components introduced:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- FastAPI Server[m
[32m+[m[32m- API Routes[m
[32m+[m[32m- Request Models[m
[32m+[m[32m- Response Models[m
[32m+[m[32m- Dependency Injection[m
[32m+[m[32m- Exception Handlers[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mExisting business modules required no architectural redesign.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Validation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mSuccessfully validated through:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- 90 / 90 Automated Tests[m
[32m+[m[32m- REST API Integration Tests[m
[32m+[m[32m- OpenAPI Validation[m
[32m+[m[32m- Swagger Validation[m
[32m+[m[32m- End-to-End Pipeline Execution[m
[32m+[m[32m- Sample Dataset[m
[32m+[m[32m- Large Dataset[m
[32m+[m[32m- Stress Dataset[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Future Impact[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThis decision establishes the foundation for:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Sprint 9 — Power BI Integration[m
[32m+[m[32m- Sprint 10 — React Frontend[m
[32m+[m[32m- Sprint 11 — AI Services[m
[32m+[m[32m- Sprint 12 — Production Deployment[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mNo additional architectural changes should be required for exposing[m
[32m+[m[32mnew services through REST APIs.[m
[32m+[m
