[32m+[m[32m# ADR-012 — API Request & Response Contracts[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Status:** Accepted[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Date:** 23 July 2026[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Sprint:** Sprint 8 — REST API Integration[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Version:** v8.0.0[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Context[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIntroducing a REST API Layer required a standardized mechanism[m
[32m+[m[32mfor exchanging data between external clients and AnalystGPT Enterprise.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWithout formal contracts:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Clients become dependent on implementation details.[m
[32m+[m[32m- API evolution becomes unpredictable.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Validation becomes inconsistent.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Documentation cannot be generated automatically.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mA contract-first approach was selected to preserve long-term API stability.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Decision[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAdopt strongly typed request and response models using Pydantic.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mEvery endpoint must:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Accept a defined request model.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Return a defined response model.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Validate requests before business execution.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Serialize responses consistently.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe API contract becomes the public interface of the application.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Contract Flow[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```text[m
[32m+[m[32mHTTP Request[m
[32m+[m[32m      │[m
[32m+[m[32m      ▼[m
[32m+[m[32mPipelineRequest[m
[32m+[m[32m      │[m
[32m+[m[32m      ▼[m
[32m+[m[32mApplication.run()[m
[32m+[m[32m      │[m
[32m+[m[32m      ▼[m
[32m+[m[32mPipelineResult[m
[32m+[m[32m      │[m
[32m+[m[32m      ▼[m
[32m+[m[32mPipelineResponse[m
[32m+[m[32m      │[m
[32m+[m[32m      ▼[m
[32m+[m[32mHTTP Response[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Request Contracts[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCurrent request models include:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- PipelineRequest[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mResponsibilities:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Validate input[m
[32m+[m[32m- Define required fields[m
[32m+[m[32m- Reject invalid requests[m
[32m+[m[32m- Provide automatic documentation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Response Contracts[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mCurrent response models include:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- APIResponse[m
[32m+[m[32m- RootResponse[m
[32m+[m[32m- HealthResponse[m
[32m+[m[32m- VersionResponse[m
[32m+[m[32m- PipelineResponse[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mResponsibilities:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Stable output[m
[32m+[m[32m- Consistent serialization[m
[32m+[m[32m- Strong typing[m
[32m+[m[32m- Automatic OpenAPI generation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Consequences[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Positive[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Stable client interfaces.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Automatic validation.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Consistent API responses.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Simplified documentation.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Improved maintainability.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Easier automated testing.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Backward compatibility becomes manageable.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Negative[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Contract changes require careful version management.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Additional models increase repository size.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Public interfaces require long-term maintenance.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Alternatives Considered[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Dictionary Responses[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mRejected.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mReason:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWeak typing increases maintenance risk and reduces documentation quality.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Untyped Requests[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mRejected.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mReason:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mValidation would become inconsistent and error-prone.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Direct DataFrame Exchange[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mRejected.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mReason:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mInternal implementation details should never be exposed through public APIs.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Design Principles Preserved[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Contract-driven Development[m
[32m+[m[32m- Strong Typing[m
[32m+[m[32m- Separation of Concerns[m
[32m+[m[32m- Stable Interfaces[m
[32m+[m[32m- API-first Architecture[m
[32m+[m[32m- Backward Compatibility[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Implementation Impact[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mNew models introduced:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- PipelineRequest[m
[32m+[m[32m- PipelineResponse[m
[32m+[m[32m- RootResponse[m
[32m+[m[32m- HealthResponse[m
[32m+[m[32m- VersionResponse[m
[32m+[m[32m- APIResponse[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThese contracts define the public interface while allowing[m
[32m+[m[32minternal implementations to evolve independently.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Validation[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mContracts validated through:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Request Validation[m
[32m+[m[32m- Response Validation[m
[32m+[m[32m- Swagger UI[m
[32m+[m[32m- OpenAPI Specification[m
[32m+[m[32m- Integration Tests[m
[32m+[m[32m- Endpoint Tests[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAll validations completed successfully.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m# Future Impact[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mFuture endpoints should continue using:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Strong typing[m
[32m+[m[32m- Stable contracts[m
[32m+[m[32m- Versioned interfaces[m
