[32m+[m[32m# Sprint 8 — REST API Lessons[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## REST API Design[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- REST APIs expose services rather than business logic.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Resource-oriented endpoints improve long-term maintainability.[m
[32m+[m[32m- A thin API Layer simplifies future integrations.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Stable endpoints reduce client-side changes.[m
[32m+[m[32m- HTTP methods should align with operations.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Status codes should communicate intent clearly.[m
[32m+[m[32m- API versioning should be planned from the beginning.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Dependency Injection[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Dependency Injection improves testability.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Dependencies should be provided rather than constructed.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Lifecycle management belongs to infrastructure.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Business modules should not manage dependencies.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Application dependencies should be centralized.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Dependency Injection reduces global state.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Explicit dependencies improve code clarity.[m
[32m+[m
