[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Architectural Principles Preserved[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Single Responsibility Principle** — API Layer handles HTTP concerns only.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Separation of Concerns** — Business logic remains isolated in the Application Layer.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Loose Coupling** — API Layer communicates only through stable contracts.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **High Cohesion** — All API-related components are contained within the API package.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Layered Architecture** — Each layer has a clear, distinct responsibility.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Key Architectural Decisions[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- API Layer contains zero business logic.[m
[32m+[m[32m- All pipeline execution is delegated to the Application Layer.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Dependency Injection manages Application lifecycle.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Pydantic models handle request validation and response serialization.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Global exception handlers provide consistent error responses.[m
[32m+[m[32m- OpenAPI documentation is generated automatically from code.[m
